A businessman, Daniel Hogan, 43, on Wednesday appeared in an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court in Lagos for allegedly defrauding his lover of N2.5 million. <img class="size-full wp-image-1265514 aligncenter" src="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=640%2C360&#038;ssl=1" alt="Marketing officer docked for allegedly stealing laptops worth N3.11m" width="640" height="360" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=300%2C169&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=768%2C432&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=1024%2C576&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=260%2C146&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=200%2C113&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i2.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/court-symbol.jpg?resize=560%2C315&amp;ssl=1 560w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Hogan, who resides in Calabar, is charged with conspiracy, obtaining money under pretence and stealing, which he pleaded not guilty. The Prosecution Counsel, Sgt. Adetutu Sanusi told the court that Hogan collected N2.5 million from his girlfriend, Miss Lilian Ojeikere to pay for a spiritualist to pray for her to enable her to travel abroad. She also said that the defendant threatened to kill Ojeikere. The prosecution alleged that Hogan stole the complainant’s Samsung A8 phone valued at N300,000. Sanusi said that the defendant and other persons, who are at large, committed the offence on July 2, at Foursquare Church, Shasha, Lagos. The offence, she said,  contravened the provisions of sections 411, 285 and 314 of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. Magistrate O.C. Emeka-Okpara admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N500,000 bail with two sureties in like sum. Emeka-Okpara adjourned the case until Oct. 30 for hearing. Vanguard For allegedly defrauding his estranged lover of N5 million on the pretext of investing it in a business, a 35-year-old estate agent, Gbeminiyi Babajide, on Tuesday appeared before an Ikeja Magistrates’ Court. December 4, 2018 In "News" The police on Thursday arraigned a bureau de change operator, Arinze Onwudiwe,  in an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, Lagos for allegedly defrauding a businessman of N17.9 million. October 3, 2019 In "News" A 43-year-old businessman, John Ebiekpi, who allegedly defrauded his business partner of N12 million on Monday appeared at an Igbosere Magistrates’ Court, Lagos. December 24, 2018 In "Crime Alert"